        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24472",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "* cacheenabled\nThis would bring exactly nothing.\nDon't add a cache and it will not be used.\nGenerally you should always use cache.\n\n* cacheid\nAlso this brings exactly nothing.\nEach file is stored in it's own cacheid.\nAnd when you use a file in two adapters it would be nonsense to have it also stored twice when the data is the same.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T04:45:41.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T04:45:41.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24477",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Thomas,\n\n   Please forgive the direct email. I can't seem to add comments to the JIRA issue.\n\n\n\ncacheenabled\nThis would bring exactly nothing.\nDon't add a cache and it will not be used.\nGenerally you should always use cache.\n\nThe problem is that the cache is static so if it is set by something else then it automatically gets used. Without this option I would have to save the current translation cache instance to a temp variable, clear the translation cache (which from looking at the Zend_Translate_Adapter::setCache signature you cant do as it expects an instance of Zend_Cache_Core), then create the non cached adapter instance and then restore the translation cache.\n\n\ncacheid\nAlso this brings exactly nothing.\nEach file is stored in it's own cacheid.\nAnd when you use a file in two adapters it would be nonsense to have it also stored twice when the data is the same.\n\nFrom looking at the code the cache id is simply the translation adapter name and is therefore tied to the adapter and not the translation files. I agree that it would be nonsense to have the data stored twice if the same file is used in two adapters, this is not what i'm asking. What i'm asking is to be able to have two adapters using two different files. Currently if the static cache is set then you can only have one instance of any adapter as the cache id is linked to the adapter class name and not to the translation files which they reference.\n\n-- \nRegards,\nWilliam Bailey\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T05:53:56.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T05:53:56.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24478",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "When you can add a disableCache() then you can also do a setCache(null); \nwhich is exactly the same or change the cache to a mock cache.\nBut this are things from the cache and not related to translations. \nGenerally such features, if needed, should be used across the framework and \nnot only be added in only one component. Actually I see no benefit for a \ndisableCache method.\n\nAnd the id line\n$id = 'Zend_Translate_' . preg_replace('\/[^a-zA-Z0-9_]\/', '_', $data) . '_' \n. $locale . '_' . $this->toString();\nshows you that you are wrong. The full path, filename and locale is used for \nthe cacheid.\n\nPS: Please comment always your issues so others can follow your suggestions \nand the complete workflow.\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-12T05:54:18.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-12T05:54:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24634",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "No need for this feature seen.\n\nID is actually directory-file based.\nAnd dis\/enabling the can simply be done by setting a empty cache, null, or a mock cache.\n\nIssue closed due to no additionally response.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-23T10:35:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-23T10:35:47.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
